And to answer your question on whether with or without image is better: it depends. Because I think that's actually not the important criteria. I can see that if we post on time (1-5 minutes within the time the author posted) and high quality content of text in the post, we can easily get high impressions.

Another point that I notice is that we actually have to curate a list of suitable KOLs, because replies in Elon Musk posts often flop even though it's quite on time and I can see the replies are quite funny and memeable. But replies on Hayes, CZ, Saylor tends to get much better impressions

